  <h2 id="philosophy">Pure Core / Impure Shell</h2>

  <p>
    This pattern has a name in functional and systems design: <strong>Functional Core, Imperative Shell</strong>. The core contains all logic — pure functions, no side effects. The shell manages effects — I/O, network, time — and feeds results into the core.
  </p>

